      "level": {
        "value": 15
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> Bishop of Scarwall, Kazavon's religious adviser — a lich whose own <em>forbiddance</em> gambit backfired: sealed into his donjon by Mandraivus's counter-wards, he ordered his followers' ritual suicides, and then the curse's necromantic detonation focused on the chapel and blasted him to dust, remaking him a <strong>demilich</strong>. A jeweled skull drifting over the Dark Shrine's altar (F11). The hardest anchor — unless the party never wakes him at all. <strong>Treasure is his body:</strong> two ruby eyes (~250 gp each) and ten ruby teeth (~100 gp each) — some holding screaming souls; beneath his ashes on the altar lie a <em>strand of prayer beads (greater)</em> and a <em>+2 striking spiked chain with a speed rune</em>, revealed when the ashes fly up.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
